 Bridge sunset 2026","Golden Gate Bridge sunset photos 2026"],"query":"site:unsplash.com Golden Gate Bridge sunset 2026","sources":[{"type":"url","url":"https://www.sfchronicle.com/sf/article/july-fourth-fireworks-golden-gate-bridge-22306092.php"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.sfgate.com/local/article/golden-gate-bridge-fireworks-22306510.php"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-at-sunset-with-city-skyline-suvaaoX7xdQ"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-emerging-from-fog-at-dusk-So_P3sAmhh4"},{"type":"url","url":"https://flickr.com/photos/tags/streetsofsf"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/the-golden-gate-bridge-spans-across-the-water-67Sfnfo50SI"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/suspension-bridge-over-water-at-sunset-dAzxhSMAoFM"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/close-up-of-the-golden-gate-bridge-towers-against-sky-BqjoyB4-XoQ"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/83189681%40N00/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DVhu26NjGBA/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-seen-through-a-frame-of-padlocks-ynXMCbF_o_w"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/jmsf415/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.facebook.com/groups/SFbayareastreetphotograpy/posts/10165161151140746/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/187137533%40N06/favorites/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-over-water-with-a-mountain-backdrop-K4097es3zcA"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/tags/Polaroid%20Impulse%20AF/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/bay-bridge-at-sunset-with-dramatic-clouds-vKk4P2_sbZ0"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/cargo-ship-passes-under-golden-gate-bridge-rlJ7hIiyjyA"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/44548980%40N00/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://stock.adobe.com/search?k=golden+gate+bridge+sunset"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DS-u-X-EhbQ/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://sarowly.me/blog/bestgoldengateviewpoints"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DS_xSSVjt5U/"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.istockphoto.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-sunset"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-at-sunset-with-city-skyline-suvaaoX7xdQ?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-emerging-from-fog-at-dusk-So_P3sAmhh4?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/suspension-bridge-over-water-at-sunset-dAzxhSMAoFM?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-over-water-with-a-mountain-backdrop-K4097es3zcA?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/the-golden-gate-bridge-spans-across-the-water-67Sfnfo50SI?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.goldengate.org/?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.nps.gov/goga/planyourvisit/placestogo.htm?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.parksconservancy.org/parks/golden-gate-bridge?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.parksconservancy.org/park-e-ventures-article/jaw-dropping-sunset-spots-our-parks?utm_source=openai"},{"type":"url","url":"https://www.sfchronicle.com/sf/article/july-fourth-fireworks-golden-gate-bridge-22306092.php?utm_source=openai"}]},"results":[{"type":"text_result","snippet":"citeturn1news27 [wordlim: 100] Published: 6 days ago; San Francisco will celebrate the United States' 250th birthday with a rare fireworks show launched from the Golden Gate Bridge on July 4, 2026, as announced by Mayor Daniel Lurie. This marks only the third time fireworks have been launched from the iconic bridge, following celebrations in 1987 and 2012 for the bridge's 50th and 75th anniversaries, respectively. The fireworks will be set off from the east side of the bridge, including the tops of the two towers and from two barges—one near the bridge and another by Pier 39. The show is scheduled to begin around 9:30 p.m., with large crowds expected. Suggested viewing spots include Crissy Field, Marina Green, and the northern Embarcadero, while areas like the Ferry Building will not offer views this year. The bridge will be fully closed to vehicle traffic during the event, and pedestrian access on the east sidewalk will be partially restricted.\nS.F. plans rare Golden Gate Bridge fireworks show for July Fourth\nDate: Mon Jun 15 18:48:35 2026 UTC\n\nSan Francisco will celebrate the country's 250th birthday by setting off fireworks from the Golden Gate Bridge on July Fourth, Mayor Daniel Lurie said Monday.\nIt will be just the third time the iconic bridge has ever hosted such a pyrotechnics display, following previous instances in 1987 and 2012 - when the bridge turned 50 and 75 years old, respectively.\nThis year's official Fourth of July fireworks show will happen on the east side of the bridge on top of and in between its two towers, with two barges also in the bay, one near the bridge and one by Pier 39, according to the city. (In previous years, barges were positioned by Pier 39 and near Aquatic Park.) The show will start at about 9:30 p.m., but onlookers are encouraged to get to a vantage point well before that due to the expected crowds.\n\"The Golden Gate Bridge is as iconic as any landmark in the United States, so it's an ideal place to launch fireworks for our country's 250th anniversary,\" Lurie said in a statement.\nCity officials suggested viewing spots such as Crissy Field, Marina Green and the northern Embarcadero, including along Pier 39 or the area around Taylor and Jefferson streets. The Ferry Building and eastern Embarcadero won't have views of the fireworks this year. \nThe bridge will be completely closed to traffic during the July Fourth fireworks show, and the sidewalk on the east side of the bridge will be partially shut down beforehand, officials said.\n","title":"S.F. plans rare Golden Gate Bridge fireworks show for July Fourth","url":"https://www.sfchronicle.com/sf/article/july-fourth-fireworks-golden-gate-bridge-22306092.php"},{"type":"text_result","snippet":"citeturn1news28 [wordlim: 100] Published: 6 days ago; San Francisco is planning a major fireworks display for the 250th anniversary of the United States on July 4, 2026, marking only the third time fireworks will be launched from the iconic Golden Gate Bridge. According to Mayor Daniel Lurie's office, the show will begin around 9:30 PM and be visible from various parts of San Francisco and the Bay Area. However, visibility concerns loom due to the city's infamous July fog, often dubbed \"No-Sky July.\" The city remains hopeful, aiming for a tourism boost following a record-breaking Memorial Day at San Francisco International Airport.\n\nThe event will require significant closures, including the Golden Gate Bridge from 8:30 PM and its surrounding pedestrian areas. Fireworks will also be launched from two barges—one near the bridge and one by Pier 39—and between the east-side bridge towers. Notably, the display will not be visible from the Ferry Building or Embarcadero waterfront. This will be the first such bridge display since the celebrations for the bridge’s 50th and 75th anniversaries in 1987 and 2012, which were both successful despite weather concerns.\n\"The historic fireworks display builds on the Lurie administration's work to welcome visitors to San Francisco, with tourism on track to break records in 2026 following San Francisco International Airport's busiest-ever Memorial Day,\" reads the release.\nThe Golden Gate Bridge is slated to be shut down from 8:30 p.m. to just after the event. Bridge sidewalks and the south-end parking lot are also set to experience closures.\nFireworks will be launched from two barges - one by the Golden Gate Bridge and another near Pier 39 - and between the two towers on the east side of the bridge, according to the release. Unlike prior years, the show won't be viewable from the Ferry Building or the Embarcadero waterfront.\nThe two other times fireworks have been launched from the iconic landmark were to celebrate the bridge's 50th and 75th anniversaries in May 1987 and May 2012. While both of those shows were visible to folks, skeptics wonder if the July extravaganza will just result in loud explosions lighting up a foggy sky. \n","title":"SF's biggest July Fourth fireworks show in decades comes with one catch","url":"https://www.sfgate.com/local/article/golden-gate-bridge-fireworks-22306510.php"},{"type":"text_result","snippet":"citeturn1search0 [wordlim: 200] Published: 2 months ago; Content type: text/html; The golden gate bridge spans across the bay. Aerial view of traffic moving on Golden Gate Bridge during sunset, San Francisco, California.\nImage: Golden gate bridge at sunset with city skyline\n\nImage: Golden gate bridge at sunset with city skyline\n\n––– –– ––\n\n––– –––– ––––\n\n––– –– ––\n\n––– –––– ––––\n\nA forward-right arrow Share Info icon Info More Actions \n\n# Golden gate bridge at sunset with city skyline \n\nDownload this free HD photo of san francisco, fog, golden gate bridge, and travel destination by Leo_Visions (@leo_visions_)\n\nCalendar outlined Published on March 28, 2026 (UTC)CameraCanon, EOS R3 Safety Free to use under the Unsplash License\n\nsan franciscofoggolden gate bridgetravel destinationurban landscapemorning lightcalifornia coastsuspension bridgecoastal cityiconic landmark\n\n","title":"Golden gate bridge at sunset with city skyline photo","url":"https://unsplash.com/photos/golden-gate-bridge-at-sunset-with-city-skyline-suvaaoX7xdQ"},{"type":"text_result","snippet":"citeturn1search2 [wordlim: 200] Published: 4 months ago; Content type: text/html; Feb 3, 2026 — Aerial view of traffic moving on Golden Gate Bridge during sunset, San Francisco, California · a view of the golden gate brid